node.contents: It's basically a Jar that you can load in and control with JavaScript. It works great, I'd highly recommend it to anyone needing similar functionality. However, since the Jar was not signed, every time the page loads, it shows a security warning. It's a little annoying and I thought that if I self-signed the Jar, it would have the 'Never show me this again' / 'Allow Forever' check box enabled. This is to be deployed internally to our organization, so signing it with a paid cert doesn't seem necessary.

node.contents: The problem is that as soon as I sign the Jar, it doesn't work. I get a class not found error. I've looked at dozens of sites that show you how to sign Jar files and googled this to page 10, and I can't find anyone that's had this kind of issue.
